HEADWORD: Deliberately
<hw>De*lib"er*ate*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With
careful consideration, or deliberation; circumspectly; warily; not
hastily or rashly; slowly; <as>as, a purpose <ex>deliberately</ex>
formed</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

